canOpenAsDataRaster

protected static boolean canOpenAsDataRaster(Object source,
                                             AVList params)
Returns true if the specified input source is non-null and represents a data raster (imagery or elevation), and false otherwise. The input source may be one of the following:
  • String
  • File
  • URL
  • URI
  • InputStream
Supported input source formats are:
  • BIL (Band Interleaved by Line)

Parameters:
source - the input source reference to test as a data raster.
Returns:
true if the input source is data raster, and false otherwise.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if the input source is null.

getDefaultImportLocation

public static File getDefaultImportLocation(FileStore fileStore)
Returns a location in the specified FileStore which should be used as the default location for importing data. This attempts to use the first FileStore location marked as an "install" location. If no install location exists, this falls back to the FileStore's default write location, the same location where downloaded data is cached.

The returned File represents an abstract path, and therefore may not exist. In this case, the caller must create the missing directories composing the abstract path.

Parameters:
fileStore - the FileStore to determine the default location for importing data.
Returns:
the default location in the specified FileStore to be used for importing data.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if the FileStore is null.

isImageData

public static boolean isImageData(Object source)
Returns true if the specified input source is non-null and represents image data, and false otherwise. The input source may be one of the following:
  • String
  • File
  • URL
  • URI
  • InputStream
Supported input source formats are:
  • BMP (with georeferencing file)
  • GeoTIFF
  • GIF (with georeferencing file)
  • JPEG (with georeferencing file)
  • PNG (with georeferencing file)
  • RPF (Raster Product Format)
  • TIFF (with georeferencing file)
  • WBMP (with georeferencing file)
  • X-PNG (with georeferencing file)

Parameters:
source - the input source reference to test as image data.
Returns:
true if the input source is image data, and false otherwise.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if the input source is null.
